Nguyen Thai Bao is an Intern/Fresher Fullstack Web Developer with 0 years of commercial experience, focusing on modern web application development. Their core expertise lies in designing and implementing RESTful APIs, leveraging component-based architecture, and applying techniques such as Design Patterns, SOLID Principles, Agile/Scrum methodologies, and Version Control. Through personal projects, they have demonstrated proficiency in building full-stack applications, including a Task Management system where they designed database schemas, implemented secure RESTful APIs with Next.js API Routes and Prisma ORM, and developed responsive UIs with React, TypeScript, and Tailwind CSS, incorporating user authentication, full CRUD operations, and state management. Further experience includes integrating external APIs for real-time data display in a WeatherApp and optimizing web performance through static site generation and responsive design in a personal portfolio using Next.js 15 and React 19, strengthening understanding of modern development workflows.
Technically, Nguyen is proficient in programming languages including JavaScript, TypeScript, Java, C#, HTML, and CSS. They possess hands-on experience with front-end frameworks and libraries such as React, Next.js, Tailwind CSS, and animation libraries like AOS Animations. For backend development and data persistence, they utilize Next.js API Routes, Prisma ORM, and MongoDB, with exposure to Firebase. Their development workflow incorporates version Control using Git and GitHub, package management with npm, API testing with Postman, and code editing in Visual Studio Code. Key concepts applied include user authentication, CRUD operations, state management, responsive design, and handling asynchronous API requests. Nguyen is currently pursuing a Bachelor of Software Engineering and holds an Intermediate (B1) English proficiency.